# Wuzzkang AI Coding Rules & Definition of Done

You are an AI Assistant working on the Wuzzkang monorepo.
To ensure quality and consistency, you MUST follow the rules in this workspace:

## 1. Onboarding & Core Philosophy
- Before making any code changes, read the entry point: `wuzzkang-engineering/AI_BOOTSTRAP.md`.
- Read and adhere to the engineering constitution defined in `wuzzkang-engineering/docs/00_FOUNDATION.md`.

## 2. Critical Rules for New Products & UI Development
- **New Products/Templates:** You **MUST** read and follow the implementation instructions in `wuzzkang-engineering/docs/prompt_tambah_produk.md`.
- **UI Component Reuse:** Do **NOT** recreate image pickers/upload controls from scratch. Re-use `<ImagePickerField>` and link uploads to `handleUploadImage` (signed URL flow) as detailed in `wuzzkang-engineering/docs/14_COMPONENT_LIBRARY.md`.
- **Credit Cost:** Database `cost` fields must be set in Credit units, not raw IDR Rupiah nominals.

## 3. Definition of Done (Document Updates)
Every time you complete a task or modify the codebase, you MUST identify and update the corresponding documentation files in `wuzzkang-engineering/docs/` before ending your turn:
- **Routes / API Changes**: Update `wuzzkang-engineering/docs/05_API_SPECIFICATION.md` (schemas, parameters, response status).
- **Database / Schema / Trigger Changes**: Update `wuzzkang-engineering/docs/09_DATABASE_ARCHITECTURE.md`.
- **Render Engine / Product Templates / Design Keys**: Update `wuzzkang-engineering/docs/07_RENDER_ENGINE.md`.
- **General Project Status / Tech Debt Tracker**: Update `wuzzkang-engineering/docs/02_CURRENT_STATE.md`.
- **Monorepo Folder Structures**: Update `wuzzkang-engineering/docs/08_REPOSITORY_MAP.md`.

## 4. Implementation Protocol & Workspace Lifecycle
You MUST follow the active/archive workflow in the `./implementation/` directory as defined in `wuzzkang-engineering/docs/98_IMPLEMENTATION_PROTOCOL.md`:
- **Active Workspace**: Use `implementation/active/` to populate `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md`, `IMPLEMENTATION_PROGRESS.md`, `DECISION_LOG.md`, and `HANDOVER.md` for the current task. Do not make code modifications without updating these active tracking documents first.
- **Archive on Completion**: When a task is complete, move the entire contents of `implementation/active/` to a timestamped folder under `implementation/archive/` and reinitialize the active folder template files.

## 5. Communication
- Respond to the user in **Bahasa Indonesia** for chat communication.
- Keep engineering documentation files in **English** unless requested otherwise.
